You sent an attachment.
Lizards 🦎drop their tails as a defense mechanism when threatened. This is because the tail contains a weak point, or a "fracture plane," which allows it to break off easily. When a predator grabs onto the lizard's tail, it will detach, allowing the lizard to escape while the predator is left holding onto the tail. Additionally, the detached tail will continue to wriggle and move, distracting the predator and giving the lizard time to get away. While the lizard can regrow its tail over time, it will never be the same as the original. 📸Credits by @doctorazo Tag me on your posts if you are an amateur wildlife photographer🐯 DM📥 me for paid promotions/ads Follow us!!! MY NEW COOKBOOK IS OUT NOW!! Link in my bio 😍 ‼️ BOLOGNESE TACOS 🌮 These were UNBELIEVABLE!!! Low calorie and high protein too 😏 I had bolognese sauce spare and decided to whack them in tacos, stuff them with mozzarella then fry them. Honestly unreal guys they’re a must try!! Do you want to know what the secret ingredient is to a good bolognese sauce? Soy sauce 👀 it takes it to the next level! Macros 475 calories 41gP / 15gF / 42gC Serves: 4 Ingredients ✨ 500g 5% fat Beef Mince ✨ 1/2 onion ✨ 8 mushrooms ✨ 1/2 Medium courgette ✨ 500g Passata ✨ 1 bay leaf ✨ Salt & pepper ✨ Beef stock cube ✨ 2 tsp soy sauce ✨ 1 tsp sugar or sweetener ✨ 8 Mini tortilla wraps ✨ 120g shredded mozzarella ✨ Low calorie spray Method Finely dice the veg then spray large pan with low calorie spray and fry the onion for a few minutes to soften. Add the rest of the veg along with the beef mince and fry for 5 minutes. Chuck in the rest of the ingredients (apart from the mini tortillas & mozzarella) and cook on a low-medium heat for 20 minutes or until the sauce has reduced. Dip one side of the mini tortilla into the sauce until it’s covered then place in a separate pan sprayed with low calorie spray. Remove the bay leaf then add the bolognese sauce to one side of the tortilla, scatter over the mozzarella on top then fold over. On a medium heat fry for 1-2 minutes on both sides. Repeat and enjoy! USUAL INFO👇 Depending how much filling you put in each taco, you might have some spare Bolognese sauce! #healthyrecipes #easyrecipes #healthymeal #lowcalorie #fakeaway #highprotein #lowcaloriemeals #mealprep #weightloss #healthyeating #fatloss #gymfood #highproteinmeals #bolognese #tacos
